==English==
===Pronunciation===
*fä(r)'si, /ˈfɑː(r)si/, /"fA:rsi/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)si|Rhymes: -ɑː(r)si]]
*fä(r)'sē, /ˈfɑː(r)siː/, /"fA:rsi:/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)siː|Rhymes: -ɑː(r)siː]]

===Etymology===
Directly from the local term for the province of Persis ("[[Fars]]") in southern Iran, adopted by Persians to refer to their language after Islamic invasions in the 7th century.

===Proper noun===
#the national language of Iran.

===Usage note===
*More formally the term [[Western Farsi]] is preferred by linguists for this language.  [[Easter Farsi]] which is often called [[Dari]] is used in Afghanistan and is very similar.  
Together with [[Tajiki]] and seven other similar languages these form the [[Persion]] language group.  Because of this, the term "Persian" should be avoided as the name of the language.

